        <!-- User Stories Section -->
        <section id="user-stories" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="section-title" data-aos="fade-up">3. User Stories</h2>
            
            <div data-aos="fade-up">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">Epic: Initial Itinerary Planning</h3>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> new user, <strong>I want to</strong> enter a simple text prompt describing my trip (e.g., "5 days in Goa for a beach vacation"), <strong>so that</strong> I can get a basic itinerary to start with.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> traveler with specific interests, <strong>I want to</strong> use preference sliders (for budget, history, food, etc.), <strong>so that</strong> the generated itinerary is tailored to my tastes.</p>
                </div>
                 <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> planner, <strong>I want to</strong> see a creative title and a summary of my trip, <strong>so that</strong> I can quickly understand the theme of the generated plan.</p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div data-aos="fade-up" class="mt-10">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">Epic: Itinerary Management & Refinement</h3>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> user, <strong>I want to</strong> modify my itinerary with another text prompt (e.g., "add more shopping"), <strong>so that</strong> I can refine my plan without restarting.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> meticulous planner, <strong>I want to</strong> drag and drop days or locations, <strong>so that</strong> I can manually reorder the schedule to my liking.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> user, <strong>I want to</strong> remove a location I'm not interested in, <strong>so that</strong> I can customize my plan.</p>
                </div>
                 <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> visual planner, <strong>I want to</strong> see all my locations on a map, <strong>so that</strong> I can understand the geography of my trip.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div data-aos="fade-up" class="mt-10">
                <h3 class="subsection-title">Epic: Advanced Features & Export</h3>
                 <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> cautious traveler, <strong>I want to</strong> run a feasibility check on my itinerary, <strong>so that</strong> I know if my daily plan is realistic in terms of travel time.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> user preparing for my trip, <strong>I want to</strong> download my itinerary as a PDF, <strong>so that</strong> I can have an offline copy.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="user-story">
                    <p><strong>As a</strong> first-time visitor, <strong>I want to</strong> get essential travel information (like visa and currency) for my destination, <strong>so that</strong> I can be well-prepared.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Requirements Section -->
        <section id="requirements" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="section-title" data-aos="fade-up">4. Requirements</h2>
            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mt-6">
                <div data-aos="fade-right">
                    <h3 class="subsection-title !mt-0">Functional Requirements</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside prose space-y-2">
                        <li>The system must accept natural language text input.</li>
                        <li>The system must generate itineraries in a structured JSON format.</li>
                        <li>The system must integrate with Google Places API to fetch location details.</li>
                        <li>The UI must dynamically render the itinerary from the JSON response.</li>
                        <li>Users must be able to modify, reorder, and delete items from the itinerary.</li>
                        <li>The system must provide an option to view all locations on a Google Map.</li>
                        <li>The system must allow exporting the itinerary to PDF and TXT formats.</li>
                        <li>The system must provide a feasibility check using a directions API.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div data-aos="fade-left">
                    <h3 class="subsection-title !mt-0">Non-Functional Requirements</h3>
                    <ul class="list-disc list-inside prose space-y-2">
                        <li><strong>Performance:</strong> Initial itinerary generation should complete within 15 seconds.</li>
                        <li><strong>Usability:</strong> The interface must be intuitive and require no training. The application must be fully responsive and mobile-friendly.</li>
                        <li><strong>Reliability:</strong> The application should have an uptime of 99.5% and handle API errors gracefully.</li>
                        <li><strong>Scalability:</strong> The backend should be able to handle at least 100 concurrent users (as per App Engine config).</li>
                        <li><strong>Security:</strong> All API keys and sensitive credentials must be stored securely as environment variables and not exposed on the client-side.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <!-- Success Metrics Section -->
        <section id="metrics" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="section-title" data-aos="fade-up">5. Success Metrics</h2>
            <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mt-6">
                <div class="card p-6" data-aos="zoom-in">
                    <i class="fas fa-users text-3xl text-indigo-500 mb-3"></i>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">User Engagement</h4>
                    <p class="prose text-sm mt-1">Number of itineraries generated per day. Average number of modification requests per session.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card p-6" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-delay="100">
                    <i class="fas fa-check-circle text-3xl text-indigo-500 mb-3"></i>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">Task Completion Rate</h4>
                    <p class="prose text-sm mt-1">Percentage of users who successfully generate and then export or view their plan on the map.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="card p-6" data-aos="zoom-in" data-aos-delay="200">
                    <i class="fas fa-rocket text-3xl text-indigo-500 mb-3"></i>
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg">Adoption & Retention</h4>
                    <p class="prose text-sm mt-1">Number of new users per week. Percentage of users who return for a second session.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>
        
        <!-- Future Considerations Section -->
        <section id="future" class="mb-16">
            <h2 class="section-title" data-aos="fade-up">6. Future Considerations (Post-MVP)</h2>
            <ul class="list-disc list-inside prose mt-4 space-y-3">
                <li data-aos="fade-left"><strong>User Accounts & Saved Itineraries:</strong> Allow users to create accounts to save, name, and manage their travel plans.</li>
                <li data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-delay="50"><strong>Collaboration:</strong> Enable sharing an itinerary with friends or family, allowing them to view or suggest edits.</li>
                <li data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-delay="100"><strong>Real-time Booking Integration:</strong> Partner with booking affiliates to allow users to book flights and hotels directly from the itinerary.</li>
                <li data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-delay="150"><strong>Multi-destination Trips:</strong> Enhance the AI prompt to handle complex trips spanning multiple cities or countries.</li>
                <li data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-delay="200"><strong>Mobile App:</strong> Develop native iOS and Android applications for a better mobile experience.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>


